# cross-machine

# Cross-Machine Workflow — Mini ↔ Main

Brad runs work across two Macs on a shared Tailscale tailnet (`tailf54584.ts.net`):

| Role | Hostname | Tailscale name | User |
|------|----------|----------------|------|
| **main** (primary pipeline machine) | MacBook Air | `brads-macbook-air` | `bflanary` |
| **mini** (secondary / control surface) | Mac mini | `brads-mac-mini` | `bflanary_mini` |

Both machines run the **open-source Tailscale CLI build** (`brew install tailscale`), which is required for the Tailscale SSH server. The sandboxed App Store / `macsys` build does NOT run the SSH server and was replaced on 2026-05-20.

## SSH Between Machines

`ssh main` from mini and `ssh mini` from main both work via Tailscale SSH (no key management, identity via Tailscale account). Aliases are in `~/.ssh/config` on each machine.

If `ssh main` fails:
- Check Tailscale is up: `tailscale status` (the other machine should appear, not "offline")
- Check the other machine ran `tailscale up --ssh` (verify with `tailscale debug prefs | grep RunSSH` on that machine — should be `true`)
- Old offline peers (e.g. the dead `brads-mac-mini` from the daemon swap) can be cleaned up at https://login.tailscale.com/admin/machines

## Canonical Machine Per Project

| Project | Canonical | Why |
|---------|-----------|-----|
| youtube-automation | **main** | Pipelines + work_dirs + OAuth tokens + gcloud + playlist rotation. Drive remotely via `ssh main` + `tmux attach -t pipeline`. |
| ops-dashboard | both | Read-only on either. Phase 2 will add a mirror helper to read main's `metrics.db` from mini. |
